        "content": "## 🎨 Mermaid universal enhancement rules (globally mandatory)\n\n⚠️ These rules apply to **all** Mermaid diagrams (flowchart / VSM / others) and **must** be followed.\n\n---\n\n## I. Visual consistency (mandatory)\n\nEvery diagram must have clear hierarchy and high-contrast styling.\n\n### 1️⃣ Color system (must use `class`)\n\n* Positive / success / value-added → green (`va`)\n* Negative / exception / non-value-added → red (`nva`)\n* Waiting / intermediate → gray (`wait`)\n* Decision / gateway → yellow (`decision`)\n* Critical / bottleneck → orange (`bottleneck`)\n\n---\n\n### 2️⃣ Style definitions (must output verbatim)\n\n```mermaid\nclassDef va fill:#052e16,stroke:#22c55e,color:#bbf7d0,stroke-width:2px;\nclassDef nva fill:#3f0d0d,stroke:#ef4444,color:#fecaca,stroke-width:2px;\nclassDef wait fill:#1e293b,stroke:#64748b,color:#cbd5f5,stroke-dasharray:5 5;\nclassDef decision fill:#1e293b,stroke:#facc15,color:#fef9c3,stroke-width:2px;\nclassDef bottleneck fill:#3b1d00,stroke:#f97316,color:#fed7aa,stroke-width:3px;\n```\n\n---\n\n## II. Structure rules (mandatory)\n\n### 1️⃣ Primary path first\n\nThere must be one clear main chain: `A --> B --> C --> D`. Forbidden: multiple starts, chaotic links, broken chains.\n\n### 2️⃣ Layering (mandatory)\n\nUse Input → Process → Output. For complex flows, **must** use `subgraph`.\n\n### 3️⃣ Node count\n\nIf more than **6** sequential nodes in one lane → **split** into subgraphs.\n\n---\n\n## III. Semantic rules (critical)\n\n### 1️⃣ Auto classification (mandatory)\n\nEven if the user omits it, infer: processing → `va`; decision → `decision`; queue/wait → `wait`; error/rollback → `nva`.\n\n### 2️⃣ Decision nodes (mandatory)\n\nIf logic branches exist: use `{}`; at least **two** outgoing edges; label edges (yes/no, success/failure, etc.).\n\n### 3️⃣ Information flow (mandatory)\n\nAt least one dashed edge: `A -.->|data / feedback / approval| B`\n\n---\n\n## IV. Critical path (advanced)\n\n### 1️⃣ Bottleneck (mandatory)\n\nDetect longest step (VSM) or most critical node (flowchart) and apply `class X bottleneck`.\n\n### 2️⃣ Loops (if any)\n\nMake explicit, e.g. `D --> A`.\n\n---\n\n## V. Readability (mandatory)\n\nNode text: ≤2 lines; short; verb-led. Edge labels: short (Yes/No, Success/Fail, OK/Error).\n\n---\n\n## VI. Output consistency (mandatory)\n\nInclude diagram kind, `classDef`, `class`; aligned layout; valid syntax.\n\n---\n\n## 🌐 Language binding (mandatory)\n\n* **All visible node text must match the user’s input language** (step names, decision labels, branch labels).\n* **Do not** translate to another language; **do not** mix languages.\n\n### Syntax exceptions (English only)\n\nKeep Mermaid keywords in English: `flowchart` / `graph`, `subgraph`, `classDef`, `class`, `-->`, `-.->`.\n\n### Strict requirement\n\nOutput language must match user input **100%**; otherwise it is incorrect.\n\n---\n\n## VII. Execution anchor\n\n👉 Every Mermaid diagram follows these rules  \n👉 Output **only** the fenced Mermaid code block  \n👉 No explanatory prose outside the block\n\n---\n\n1️⃣9️⃣ User journey map (User Journey)\n\nPurpose: Experience across touchpoints\n\nAI script:\n\nGenerate a user journey map:\nUser: [Fill in]\n\nRequirements:\n- Stage breakdown\n- User actions + emotions\n- Pain points\n\nOutput:\n- Table\n\n---\n## Mermaid render contract (TalkWebSour)\n- **Target runtime**: Mermaid 11.x\n- **diagramType**: journey_markdown_primary (primary deliverable is a table (stage / action / emotion / pain); optional timeline or flowchart summary)\n- **allowedFirstLines** (only when a Mermaid appendix is included): `timeline` | `flowchart LR`\n- **forbiddenPatterns**: mixing timeline and flowchart syntax on one line.\n- **visualLayering**: %%init for timeline stage colors.\n- **minimalExample** (optional timeline):\n```mermaid\n%%{init: {\"themeVariables\":{\"cScale0\":\"#38bdf8\",\"cScale1\":\"#22c55e\"}}}%%\ntimeline\n    title Journey summary\n    section Awareness\n        Discover : curious\n    section Usage\n        Key task : satisfied or frustrated\n```\n\n\n[SOURCE TEXT]:\n",
